article.headline: Tulane 78, N. Carolina A&amp,T 54
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Kris Richard scored 19 points and Tulane tied a school record with 13 3-pointers to defeat North Carolina A&T 78-54 on Wednesday night. The Green Wave (5-7), who won two games in a row for the first time since late November, attempted 33 shots from long range, also tying a school record. Richard was 5-for-7 from beyond the arc. The Aggies (4-9), who entered the game averaging 30.8 3-point attempts per game, were 6-for-23 from long range. Tulane pulled down a season-best 47 rebounds, 16 more than North Carolina A&T, which lost its fourth straight game. The Green Wave never trailed and led 39-29 at halftime. After Nic Simpson's layup cut the deficit to eight to open the second half, Richard nailed a 3 to start a 15-2 Tulane run to keep the lead in double figures. The Green Wave had 22 assists on 28 baskets. Tavarus Alston paced the Aggies with 18 points.
